They look at people and judge rather than understanding things from their point of view. Nastiness often stems from someoneâs own lack of self esteem or happiness, I think we can all vouch for that, I think we have all been guilty of lashing out at someone undeserving because we are having a bad day.
.
Kindness is caring about others and doing things to help make their lives better. But in turn, that makes our lives better. I have had bad days, I see something and I might be jealous, in my head I might pick faults through it, because if I do that, I donât have to be jealous anymore do I? Wrong. .

And these qualities have little to do with success as we have defined it.â - David W. Orr
